--- title: Fast Food Calories subtitle: INFO 523 - Spring 2023 - Project 1 author: 'Team Algo Aces- Sai Navya Reddy Busireddy, Gowtham Theeda, Tanya Evita George, Valerie Okine, Monica Tejaswi Kommareddy' title-slide-attributes: data-background-image: images/coverimg2.jpg data-background-size: stretch data-background-opacity: '0.7' data-slide-number: none format: revealjs: theme: - data/customtheming.scss transition: concave background-transition: slide editor: visual execute: echo: false --- # Understanding the Dataset # - It consists of 18 variables that elaborate on the nutritional compostion of different fast food items. - Data has been collected from 8 different fast-food outlets. - Overall, the dataset gives a precise and clear outlook of how healthy or how harmful a certain food item can be for consumption. - Few of the main variables made use of in this project from the dataset are- 'total_fat', 'calories', 'cholestrol', 'protein. ## Question 1: ‎ ### How many calories are consumed on average per visit to each restaurant or outlet? ## Plots for question 1: ::: panel-tabset #### Plot A ![Violin plot explaining the distribution of calories per visit by restaurant.](images/output1q1.png){fig-align="center" width="720"} #### Plot B ![The plot shows the average count of calories consumed by an individual per visit to a restaurant.](images/output2q1.png){fig-align="center" width="610"} #### Insights ::: {#smallerTxt} - Content ::: ::: ## Question 2: ‎ ### How do different food item categories vary in protien-fat ratio and do they meet up to the standards of the health metric? ## Plots for question 2: ::: panel-tabset #### Plot A ![Violin Plot depicting the Protein-Fat Ratio for each restaurant.](images/output3q2.png){width="700"} #### Plot B ![Scatter Plot depicting the Protein-Fat ratio for each restaurant.](images/output4q2.png){width="700"} #### Insights ::: {#smallerTxt} - Content ::: ::: # Challenges faced: - Content. # Conclusion - On an average visit from the list of 8 outlets- Sonic, Arbys and Burger King have proved to have the most calories in that respective order. - Chick Fil-a and Subway have shown to have the largest protein-fat ratios. - Taco Bell, Sonic, Dairy Queen and Burger King have insignifact differences in their protein-fat ratios. ## ![](images/thanksimg1.gif){fig-align="center"} ## Code ::: {#7dc752dd .cell execution_count=4} ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout} ``` OLS Regression Results ============================================================================== Dep.
